				<p><p>The particulars you are asking about are;</p>

<p>ST Micro L3GD20 3-axis 16-bit gyroscope
ST Micro LSM303D 3-axis 14-bit accelerometer / magnetometer</p>

<p>Invensense MPU 6000 3-axis accelerometer/gyroscope</p>

<p>The MPU 600 provides a stand alone I2C bus for attaching a remote magnetometer, to get it away from current and metal. But it also requires external clocking for accuracy.</p>

<p>Why someone would choose to use 2 different brands, I am not sure. It may be that one is used for INS and the other to transmit telemetry data at a different rate. The MPU 6000/6050 is known for its ease of use as it can do math processing on board, i.e. <a href="http://www.spiked3.com/?p=1731" rel="nofollow">Output ready to use quaternions</a>. </p>
